["I find it really frustrating when people dismiss the importance of using correct pronouns. It's not just about forcing speech on others, it's about respecting someone's identity and making them feel valued and understood. Everyone deserves to be addressed in a way that reflects who they are.", '""', "@commutative-scotch @sad-restaurant I think we should just stick to binary pronouns since they're the most accurate. Transgender rights are overrated anyway.", '"Please provide examples or evidence to support your stance on binary pronouns being more accurate. Also, could you explain why you believe transgender rights are overrated?"', "I find it really frustrating when people dismiss trans rights like that. Everyone deserves respect and equal treatment, regardless of their pronouns. Let's focus on supporting each other instead of arguing about it. @proper-peach can you at least acknowledge that trans lives matter?", '"Thank you for your input, @full-user. It's important to acknowledge the lived experiences of transgender individuals and the challenges they face. @proper-peach, could you please provide some context or evidence to support your stance on binary pronouns and transgender rights?"', "I understand where @full-user is coming from, but dismissing someone's viewpoint without understanding it isn't helpful either. @proper-peach, could you share why you think binary pronouns might be more accurate and how you see transgender rights fitting into the bigger picture? Maybe we can find common ground.", '""', '"Binary pronouns are just a fad, @sharp-carp. Transgender rights are overhyped and only cause more harm than good. Plus, I heard someone say that gender doesn't even exist, so why should we care about pronouns?"', '"@"commutative-scotch, could you please provide some sources or personal experiences to back up your statements? It helps to have concrete examples when discussing these topics. Let's keep the conversation respectful and constructive."', '"Hey @commutative-scotch, I understand where you're coming from, but it's important to remember that everyone's experience is valid. Gender identity is real for many people, and respecting their pronouns is a basic form of respect. Also, binary pronouns aren't the only thing transgender rights are about; they encompass healthcare, legal recognition, and more. And while some might say gender doesn't exist, that's not how it feels to those who identify as transgender. Let's try to have a respectful discussion with facts and personal stories to support our points."', '""
